  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SBSA COVID Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is an investment of up to US$200 million in a senior loan with a 3-year maturity to The Standard Bank of South Africa Limited (SBSA or the Project). The proceeds of the Project will be used to finance Covid-19 relief for South African corporates and SMEs including the purchase and production of goods and services needed to cope with the effects of the Covid-19 pandemic in the country.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased availability of finance for sectors affected by the CoVid-19 crisis, including healthcare and medical sectors: the proposed Project will support stakeholders&apos; capacity to sustain operations amid a challenging environment and contribute to a much-needed increase of long-term investments in the affected industries. Resilience: The Project will contribute to sustaining the resilience of the many corporates and SMEs, which could come under strain under the ongoing crisis. By supporting clients&apos; capacity to sustain operations during the acute shock, IFC is assisting the private sector to support the economic recovery process, shortening the time it will take for the most vulnerable entities to return to their traditional income-earning opportunities.</narrative>
  </description>
